\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \strokec2 II. How Do We Repent Rightly?\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f4\b0\fs24 \cf2 Biblical repentance (Greek: 
\f5\i metanoia
\f4\i0 ) literally means a "change of mind." It is more than just feeling bad; it is a total pivot of the soul. Thomas Watson, a Puritan theologian, outlined six ingredients of true repentance that are still incredibly helpful today.\
