\f0\b \cf2 1. Sight of Sin\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f4\b0 \cf2 You cannot repent of what you will not name. A new believer must learn to stop calling sin "a mistake," "a lapse in judgment," or "just my personality." We must see sin as God sees it: an affront to His holiness and a rejection of His goodness.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf2 2. Godly Sorrow\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f4\b0 \cf2 There is a difference between "worldly sorrow" (feeling bad because you got caught or because sin ruined your reputation) and "godly sorrow" (grieving because you have offended a loving Father).\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
